"title": "5238: bribery",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5238: bribery",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The practice of offering an incentive, usually money, in order to dishonestly or illegally procure a decision or action in favour of the giver.</p>\n<h2>Bribery is sin</h2>\n<h3>It is forbidden by God on the grounds of truth and justice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:8\">EXO 23:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr19:7\">2CH 19:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:17\">DEU 10:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:18-Deut16:20\">DEU 16:18–16:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job36:18\">JOB 36:18</a></p>\n<h3>The prevalence of the sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:8\">PRO 17:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:32-Prov6:35\">PRO 6:32–6:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:14\">PRO 21:14</a></p>\n<h3>The seriousness of the sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:34\">JOB 15:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:25\">DEU 27:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:23-Isa1:24\">ISA 1:23–1:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:22-Isa5:23\">ISA 5:22–5:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:15\">ISA 33:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:12\">AMO 5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic3:9-Mic3:12\">MIC 3:9–3:12</a></p>\n<h2>The results of bribery</h2>\n<h3>Personal corruption</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:7\">ECC 7:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps26:9-Ps26:10\">PSA 26:9–26:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:10\">1TI 6:10</a></p>\n<h3>The perversion of justice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:23\">PRO 17:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:8\">EXO 23:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:19\">DEU 16:19</a></p>\n<h3>The decay of society</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:4\">PRO 29:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:12\">EZK 22:12</a> <em>Corruption, violence and decay render society subject to God's judgment.</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of bribery</h2>\n<p>Balak and Balaam:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:16\">NUM 22:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:15\">2PE 2:15</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:5\">JDG 16:5</a> <em>Delilah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:1-1Sam8:3\">1SA 8:1–8:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:2-1Sam12:3\">1SA 12:2–12:3</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:18-1Kgs15:19\">1KI 15:18–15:19</a> <em>King Asa</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:7-2Kgs16:9\">2KI 16:7–16:9</a> <em>King Ahaz</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:9\">EST 3:9</a> <em>Haman</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:14-Matt26:16\">MAT 26:14–26:16</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:10-Mark14:11\">MRK 14:10–14:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:4-Luke22:6\">LUK 22:4–22:6</a> <em>Judas</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:11-Matt28:15\">MAT 28:11–28:15</a> <em>the soldiers at the tomb</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:26\">ACT 24:26</a> <em>Governor Felix</em></p>",
